This paper deals with the evaluation of generative neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses statistical methods such as permutation-based resampling and hypothesis testing, which are relevant to the sub-field of statistics (cs.ST). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), and cs.ST.
